                <h1 id="pathways-of-power-a-guide-to-milestones-progression">Pathways of Power: A Guide to Milestones &amp; Progression</h1>
<p>This document outlines mage progression through <strong>Milestones</strong>. Each Milestone marks a new <strong>Tier</strong> of mastery in a <a href="/w/magic-system/glossary#sefirah-pl-sefirot">Sefirah</a>, unlocking new abilities and causing permanent changes.</p>
<p>There are five recognized Tiers of mastery for any given Sefirah:</p>
<h3 id="tier-0-awakening">Tier 0: Awakening</h3>
<p>The initial, often uncontrolled, opening of a pathway.</p>
<h3 id="tier-1-attunement">Tier 1: Attunement</h3>
<p>The first level of conscious control and channeling. This is the minimum requirement for <a href="/w/magic-system/glossary#cross-path-facilitation-xpy">Cross-Path Facilitation (XPY)</a>.</p>
<h3 id="tier-2-integration">Tier 2: Integration</h3>
<p>A deeper fusion of the Sefirah's concept with the mage's self.</p>
<h3 id="tier-3-dominance">Tier 3: Dominance</h3>
<p>The mage can exert the Sefirah's principles onto their environment and others.</p>
<h3 id="tier-4-ascension">Tier 4: Ascension</h3>
<p>A near-perfect embodiment of the Sefirah's concept. This is the highest known level achievable by mortals.</p>
<hr />
<h2 id="milestone-chart-template">Milestone chart template</h2>
<p>The following template is used in each Sefirah's guide. This document is a high-level summary.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th style="text-align: left;">Tier</th>
<th style="text-align: left;">Name</th>
<th style="text-align: left;">Requirement</th>
<th style="text-align: left;">Physical Change</th>
<th style="text-align: left;">Metaphysical Change</th>
<th style="text-align: left;">New Abilities Unlocked</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: left;"><strong>T0</strong></td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Awakening</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Survive an uncontrolled influx of the Sefirah's energy.</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">A subtle sign (e.g., change in eye color).</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Aura becomes visible to <a href="/w/magic-system/glossary#magic-vision">Magic-Vision</a>.</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Sporadic, uncontrolled bursts of power.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: left;"><strong>T1</strong></td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Attunement</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Consciously manifest a simple effect three times.</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">The T0 sign becomes permanent and noticeable.</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Can consciously align with the pathway; sense others with the same attunement.</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Basic channeling. Enables Cross-Path Facilitation (XPY).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: left;"><strong>T2</strong></td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Integration</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Reshape one's life to align with the Sefirah's concept.</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">A distinct, supernatural trait emerges.</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Aura develops a unique 'texture' or signature.</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Intermediate manifestations; passive environmental influence.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: left;"><strong>T3</strong></td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Dominance</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Overcome a powerful external force using the Sefirah's core principle.</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Body takes on symbolic aspects of the Sefirah (e.g., skin like marble for Binah).</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Can impose the Sefirah's concept on an area; can peer into the associated <a href="/w/world-lore/cosmology/sefirotic-realms">Sefirotic Realm</a>.</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Advanced manifestations; can create semi-permanent constructs.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: left;"><strong>T4</strong></td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Ascension</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Unique and legendary requirements.</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Transcends biology to become a living embodiment of the Sefirah.</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Becomes a 'node' on the Tree of Life; can enter their associated <a href="/w/world-lore/cosmology/sefirotic-realms">Realm</a> to establish a <strong>Domain</strong>.</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Conceptual magic; can become a <strong>Progenitor</strong> and shape their Domain's reality.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
<h2 id="high-level-summary-by-pathway">High-level summary by pathway</h2>
<p>The following is a summary of baseline abilities unlocked at <strong>Tier 1: Attunement</strong>. For full details, see the individual Sefirot guides.</p>
<h3 id="s1-keter-the-crown">S1 - Keter (The Crown)</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>T1:</strong> Minor <strong>Catalyst</strong>. <strong>XPY</strong> for <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s2-chokmah">S2</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s3-binah">S3</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s6-tiferet">S6</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="s2-chokmah-wisdom">S2 - Chokmah (Wisdom)</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>T1:</strong> Basic <strong>Magic-Vision</strong>. <strong>XPY</strong> for <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s1-keter">S1</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s3-binah">S3</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s4-chesed">S4</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s6-tiferet">S6</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="s3-binah-understanding">S3 - Binah (Understanding)</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>T1:</strong> Basic <strong>Structural Analysis</strong>. <strong>XPY</strong> for <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s1-keter">S1</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s2-chokmah">S2</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s5-gevurah">S5</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s6-tiferet">S6</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="s4-chesed-mercy">S4 - Chesed (Mercy)</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>T1:</strong> Minor <strong>Restorative Touch</strong>. <strong>XPY</strong> for <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s2-chokmah">S2</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s5-gevurah">S5</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s6-tiferet">S6</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s7-netzach">S7</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="s5-gevurah-severity">S5 - Gevurah (Severity)</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>T1:</strong> Basic <strong>Destructive Analysis</strong>. <strong>XPY</strong> for <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s3-binah">S3</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s4-chesed">S4</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s6-tiferet">S6</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s8-hod">S8</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="s6-tiferet-beauty">S6 - Tiferet (Beauty)</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>T1:</strong> <strong>Centering</strong> meditation. <strong>XPY</strong> for all adjacent paths.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="s7-netzach-victory">S7 - Netzach (Victory)</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>T1:</strong> <strong>Will to Endure</strong>. <strong>XPY</strong> for <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s4-chesed">S4</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s6-tiferet">S6</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s8-hod">S8</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s9-yesod">S9</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s10-malkuth">S10</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="s8-hod-splendor">S8 - Hod (Splendor)</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>T1:</strong> Basic <strong>Formatted Magic-Vision</strong>. <strong>XPY</strong> for <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s5-gevurah">S5</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s6-tiferet">S6</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s7-netzach">S7</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s9-yesod">S9</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s10-malkuth">S10</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="s9-yesod-foundation">S9 - Yesod (Foundation)</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>T1:</strong> <strong>Simple Phantasms</strong>. <strong>XPY</strong> for <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s6-tiferet">S6</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s7-netzach">S7</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s8-hod">S8</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s10-malkuth">S10</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="s10-malkuth-kingdom">S10 - Malkuth (Kingdom)</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>T1:</strong> <strong>Lesser Elementalism</strong> (one element). <strong>XPY</strong> for <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s7-netzach">S7</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s8-hod">S8</a>, <a href="/w/magic-system/sefirot/s9-yesod">S9</a>.</li>
</ul>
            </main>

            

